1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:03,850 --> 00:00:08,950
And so Lucky and Planer lived happily ever after.

3
00:00:11,050 --> 00:00:12,650
You won't believe what happened to me.

4
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:19,150
I was shopping, putting things on the belt, and this woman just starts screaming at me.

5
00:00:19,350 --> 00:00:21,450
You forgot to weigh your cauliflower?

6
00:00:23,150 --> 00:00:26,910
So I politely apologized and said I'd go weigh it now then.

7
00:00:27,250 --> 00:00:32,350
And she goes, oh sure, and the people behind you will just wait, we all have plenty of time, right?

8
00:00:33,350 --> 00:00:36,280
So I told her I don't care if people wait.

9
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,820
I said I want my cauliflower.

10
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:39,060
And she goes again.

11
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:41,260
You must be doing this on purpose!

12
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:42,350
Can you believe it?

13
00:00:42,850 --> 00:00:44,550
They hire nothing but psychos there.

14
00:00:45,450 --> 00:00:47,650
So I threw the cauliflower at her head.

15
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:49,100
So no cauliflower dish!

16
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:41,050
On these skis I personally beat Vit Vavra in slalom.

17
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:43,450
Now they're yours.

18
00:01:44,550 --> 00:01:45,200
They're not.

19
00:01:45,650 --> 00:01:46,650
I'm getting a snowboard.

20
00:01:47,050 --> 00:01:49,060
Well, the situation has developed differently.

21
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:49,520
How?

22
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:51,250
We don't have money.

23
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:53,720
You promised me a snowboard.

24
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,460
But Ivuska, it's just a trend.

25
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:58,600
I have a feeling in a few years nobody will care about snowboards.

26
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,020
But skis, those are a classic.

27
00:02:00,550 --> 00:02:02,350
And these you won't have to break in.

28
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:03,150
I won't, because I'm getting a snowboard.

29
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,660
You've been promising me one for four years.

30
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:09,580
But these skis were the best on the market in their day.

31
00:02:09,780 --> 00:02:11,540
Yeah, and you got a gold record in your day.

32
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,660
Don't be cheeky!

33
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:16,380
When you learn how hard it is to earn money, you'll agree with me.

34
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:19,960
Yeah, but first I'll learn what it's like to go skiing and be the only idiot with skis.

35
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:22,080
Even Sasa and Lexa will have snowboards.

36
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:22,920
Really?

37
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:23,160
Yeah.

38
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:26,300
You don't have to have everything everyone else has.

39
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,460
Try to stand out.

40
00:02:27,660 --> 00:02:29,080
Be original.

41
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:36,350
Alright, I'll leave them here, have a look but don't scratch them.

42
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:47,800
Mambo.

43
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:52,750
But this is really the last time.

44
00:02:57,050 --> 00:02:58,050
Right, that's enough.

45
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:58,820
Where to?

46
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:00,950
Two beers?

47
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:03,230
You just said you'd be here during work hours.

48
00:03:03,450 --> 00:03:05,830
And you said if I stopped drinking before noon I'd feel better.

49
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:06,550
And I don't.

50
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:08,010
Stay here.

51
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:09,430
If you feel sick, drink some water.

52
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:10,030
Some what?

53
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,620
Iva also said you don't keep your promises.

54
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:15,400
You tattled?

55
00:03:15,540 --> 00:03:16,060
I'll tattle too.

56
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:17,520
You don't take out the trash.

57
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:20,140
I'm quite surprised you even know trash gets taken out.

58
00:03:20,850 --> 00:03:23,220
At most I said I'd take it out, not that I'd keep taking it out.

59
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:24,000
I don't care.

60
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:25,600
You just don't keep your promises.

61
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:26,280
Ozzak.

62
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:29,600
So you also think I don't keep my promises?

63
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:29,920
Absolutely.

64
00:03:31,150 --> 00:03:34,550
Although, yesterday you promised to let me go home early and you didn't.

65
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:37,480
Well, a shipment came in, so obviously that wasn't possible.

66
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:39,140
Of course, you're absolutely right.

67
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:39,620
See.

68
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:43,220
And you promised I could store my Lostice Miracle here in the shop.

69
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:45,340
I haven't even seen what the hell that is yet.

70
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,350
And what the hell is it?

71
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:48,480
A delicacy.

72
00:03:48,850 --> 00:03:53,250
Cheese curds with onion pickled in beer, aged three days under a heat lamp.

73
00:03:53,350 --> 00:03:55,850
Some promises definitely should not be kept.

74
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:01,050
Obviously, right?

75
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:02,750
I'd take them.

76
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:05,450
We're not getting snowboards either in the end.

77
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,480
Adults always say something and then don't follow through.

78
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,900
You can't trust them at all.

79
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:13,380
I don't want to go skiing this year with a sled, Kropackova keeps making fun of me.

80
00:04:13,460 --> 00:04:14,760
Everyone keeps making fun of me.

81
00:04:14,860 --> 00:04:15,740
I get that.

82
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:17,450
I'd also want Bobby.

83
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:23,330
I guess we'll have to take matters into our own hands.

84
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:23,970
And how?

85
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:27,290
There's bound to be plenty of part-time jobs for students.

86
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:28,750
Ooh, Iva, that's great.

87
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:31,950
Hey, like this one.

88
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:35,450
Looking for nice, healthy girls for occasional evening work.

89
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:38,550
Hmm, you wouldn't like that.

90
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:41,150
At least I hope.

91
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:44,450
Watch the genius.

92
00:04:45,650 --> 00:04:46,950
I already know how to get a snowboard.

93
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:48,560
You ride on top.

94
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:49,800
Wanna be cool?

95
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:51,700
Win a super snowboard.

96
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:54,850
We'll ride up top, jump and also go with the teddy bear.

97
00:04:55,050 --> 00:04:57,050
That last one was my idea.

98
00:04:58,550 --> 00:04:59,290
I'm an idiot.

99
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:01,290
I almost expected something.

100
00:05:01,290 --> 00:05:01,890
Wait!

101
00:05:03,050 --> 00:05:05,310
Every five-hundredth package has a winning coupon.

102
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:07,170
This is the fifth, I have six at home.

103
00:05:07,170 --> 00:05:08,570
Just over three hundred to go.

104
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,360
They probably take out the coupons at the stores anyway.

105
00:05:12,150 --> 00:05:14,350
Sure, in stores, but they don't hire just anyone.

106
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:15,950
Not just anyone.

107
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:17,980
You too can work with us.

108
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:25,220
Are you a student, not exactly sure what minimum wage is, managed to read this ad? Harold Supermarket welcomes you to its team.

109
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,140
Positions available.

110
00:05:26,550 --> 00:05:32,150
Cash register operator, cosmetics of perishable goods, warehouse worker.

111
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:34,350
What if we tried it?

112
00:05:34,850 --> 00:05:36,250
But we couldn't handle it.

113
00:05:36,650 --> 00:05:38,170
I don't see why we couldn't.

114
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:38,530
What about me?

115
00:05:39,650 --> 00:05:40,450
You're in luck.

116
00:05:40,530 --> 00:05:41,630
They also hire the disabled.

117
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:42,370
Great!

118
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:49,450
The garbage men complained about you.

119
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:54,250
You fell asleep in front of the entrance again and they had to throw the bins over you.

120
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:54,940
So what?

121
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,340
So you, Ozzak, also don't keep your promises.

122
00:05:58,340 --> 00:05:58,640
Me?

123
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:00,340
What? That's impossible.

124
00:06:00,550 --> 00:06:02,200
And you promised you wouldn't drink so much.

125
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,580
I must have been drunk, otherwise I wouldn't have blabbed like that.

126
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:05,240
No, really.

127
00:06:05,580 --> 00:06:08,360
If I were sober and promised something, I'd keep it.

128
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:09,220
Unlike you.

129
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,240
But when I can, I keep my promises too.

130
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,040
Sure, sure.

131
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:15,520
Then why couldn't you ask the building manager if I could grow some flowers in the yard?

132
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:18,360
Because it was supposed to be hemp, poppy and jimsonweed.

133
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:23,180
And you promised to buy a bigger fridge so I don't have to keep cooling my beer in the toilet tank.

134
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:24,960
No, I said if we have the money.

135
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:27,060
You said I could fatten a pig.

136
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:27,760
At home?

137
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:30,250
At the Badger.

138
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:31,610
You're always making excuses.

139
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:33,410
You also don't keep promises.

140
00:06:34,090 --> 00:06:35,430
Look, name me one that...

141
00:06:37,650 --> 00:06:38,150
Yeah, once at auntie's cabin you promised you'd earn the Silent Beaver badge.

142
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:43,810
You were supposed to be silent for three days and you didn't do it either.

143
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,690
I got a new guitar, I had to sing.

144
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:47,870
See, you make excuses too.

145
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:48,890
Fine, have it your way.

146
00:06:49,030 --> 00:06:49,290
What?

147
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:52,250
I'll keep my promises, even years later.

148
00:06:55,450 --> 00:06:56,950
So you're going to be silent for three days?

149
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:00,350
You'll never last.

150
00:07:03,050 --> 00:07:04,250
And how will you order a beer?

151
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:10,550
Well, suit yourself.

152
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:14,650
And don't think you won't be selling normally here.

153
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:22,750
He'll never last.

154
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,880
We can't handle this.

155
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:32,700
We can.

156
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:36,750
Although learning twenty-seven types of pastry will be something.

157
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:40,780
Why does a seven-cent roll have a six-digit code?

158
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:43,650
Two, three, seven, one, eight, nine.

159
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:47,850
Two, three, seven, eight, damn.

160
00:07:47,950 --> 00:07:50,050
We can't handle this.

161
00:07:51,450 --> 00:07:54,850
A sesame bun and a sesame roll look exactly the same.

162
00:07:57,450 --> 00:08:01,950
The bun has twenty-seven seeds and the roll has forty.

163
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:02,920
I see.

164
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:06,150
Luckily I don't have to learn anything.

165
00:08:06,450 --> 00:08:07,950
The warehouse will be a breeze.

166
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,740
Did you find some disabled friends there?

167
00:08:10,060 --> 00:08:12,040
Actually, the guys are totally normal.

168
00:08:13,050 --> 00:08:15,450
Everyone's on first name terms, and when I visited, nobody was doing anything.

169
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:22,520
And look, a doughnut with strawberry jam has the exact same code as apricot, just the last number is different.

170
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:24,580
3358 and 3359.

171
00:08:24,780 --> 00:08:25,920
See, so it'll go fast.

172
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:27,600
Besides, I'll only be there briefly anyway.

173
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,950
Until I find the right door.

174
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,650
You're awfully quiet today.

175
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:42,240
Really?

176
00:08:44,990 --> 00:08:47,170
Didn't tell mom who goes to night classes.

177
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:49,670
Didn't tell Maruna to come to the Morgue tonight.

178
00:08:50,350 --> 00:08:53,830
Didn't give the exam board my excuse note that I unexpectedly died.

179
00:08:54,050 --> 00:08:56,450
Didn't give Ida's second middle name as Sepultura.

180
00:08:57,350 --> 00:08:58,250
Is that everything?

181
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:02,670
Hey, don't you want to quit this silence thing?

182
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:05,450
I won't tell anyone.

183
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:08,950
It's going to be some evening.

184
00:09:09,550 --> 00:09:10,950
Don't you want to just go home?

185
00:09:15,450 --> 00:09:17,150
I shouldn't have asked, huh?

186
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:35,650
A list of Tomas's broken promises?

187
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:36,800
What?

188
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:38,850
This.

189
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:42,060
You know why I didn't help Aunt Greta move?

190
00:09:42,450 --> 00:09:45,680
She was seventh at the Olympics in weightlifting, I'd have been useless there.

191
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:46,740
Which Olympics?

192
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:48,050
Berlin.

193
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:50,950
Well, that was quite a while ago.

194
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:53,750
You could have helped the poor old woman.

195
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:55,650
Poor?

196
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:57,750
She could have carried all three of us.

197
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:01,150
That I promised you a motorcycle for Christmas?

198
00:10:02,350 --> 00:10:05,350
I said write to Santa, and I was eight.

199
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:07,950
Jesus, how much of this is there?

200
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,950
Will you give it a rest with the methylated spirits already.

201
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:18,650
It was ages ago.

202
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:19,830
Methylated spirits?

203
00:10:19,950 --> 00:10:22,530
When we had a band, that was his favorite song.

204
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:25,330
Every time I sang it, I lost my voice for a week.

205
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:29,450
You really went into a lot of detail.

206
00:10:29,450 --> 00:10:29,890
What?

207
00:10:29,890 --> 00:10:32,350
That I didn't fix Iva's drawer?

208
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:34,450
Okay, I forgot.

209
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:38,620
Mr. Ozzak, you have to help me.

210
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:40,550
You were definitely in the army, right?

211
00:10:40,950 --> 00:10:43,450
How do you clean a floor with a toothbrush?

212
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:47,790
Beer.

213
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,150
Should I pour beer on it?

214
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,150
So not pour.

215
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:54,560
So pour?

216
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:59,760
Well, Ozzak probably can't help you, Lexa, even though you'd definitely need it.

217
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:00,580
Mr. Ozzak!

218
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:03,780
He's childishly trying to prove he keeps his promises.

219
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:06,550
He's doing the Silent Beaver, so come back the day after tomorrow.

220
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:07,760
I don't have that much time.

221
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:09,760
I have to eat my dinner off this floor tonight.

222
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:16,900
Keeping promises isn't easy, so no one can blame you for giving up.

223
00:11:17,050 --> 00:11:18,850
Or forgetting.

224
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:22,660
Tomas, don't you think something smells funny here lately?

225
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:24,450
Like something's rotting?

226
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:40,800
But what do I see?

227
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:45,450
Yeah, we're doing part-time jobs to learn the true value of money.

228
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:49,550
I commend you for taking such a responsible approach.

229
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,600
Welcome, kids, to the world of grown-ups.

230
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:54,740
Yeah, it's great, everything's smooth sailing.

231
00:11:59,410 --> 00:12:00,230
This is awful.

232
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:02,750
I can't take it anymore.

233
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:05,750
Stupid walnut snail.

234
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:09,250
That's the one code I can't remember and everyone keeps buying it like crazy.

235
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,180
772893201.

236
00:12:11,990 --> 00:12:12,430
Right.

237
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:14,850
Say it one more time.

238
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:16,780
772893201.

239
00:12:18,050 --> 00:12:19,180
Wow, you're really good now.

240
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:21,720
Yeah, what's the point if nobody comes to my register?

241
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,140
Well, you need to make yourself more visible.

242
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,480
Register open.

243
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,860
Now say it.

244
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,000
Probably not loud enough.

245
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,460
No, I'm saying it normally.

246
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,480
Register open.

247
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,560
No, I'm saying it.

248
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:34,150
Register open.

249
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:35,990
Am I supposed to scream?

250
00:12:35,990 --> 00:12:36,730
Register open!

251
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:39,450
For God's sake, don't yell in here.

252
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:41,650
At least they'd notice you.

253
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,250
And stop coming to mine all the time.

254
00:12:44,050 --> 00:12:45,320
I couldn't handle it.

255
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:48,550
Tomorrow I'm called in by the boss, she'll definitely fire me.

256
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:51,560
Look, if she tries to fire you, we'll quit too.

257
00:12:51,950 --> 00:12:52,650
Right, Lexa?

258
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:53,580
What?

259
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:56,280
Would you give up your awesome gig in the warehouse?

260
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:58,340
Well, it's not actually that awesome.

261
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:01,250
So it's not the chill place where everyone's on first name terms?

262
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:04,350
Well, the guys are pretty chill and they really are on first name terms.

263
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:06,990
Only I have to address them formally and call them sir.

264
00:13:07,350 --> 00:13:10,050
Well if that's all, you've got nothing to complain about.

265
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:10,850
I don't.

266
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:13,450
The boss said I'd better not complain anywhere.

267
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:19,050
But once I have that snowboard, nobody will ask if I had to run around the warehouse naked a hundred times.

268
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,240
What?

269
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:31,560
Good.

270
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:34,750
How are the new Black Agony?

271
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,850
Good, I'll take them.

272
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:42,840
I was also thinking about Napalm Death.

273
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:43,950
What do you think?

274
00:13:46,830 --> 00:13:47,370
Weak, huh.

275
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,840
I can see you really know your stuff.

276
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:55,550
Yeah, my buddy told me Kabati apparently put out something decent.

277
00:14:00,850 --> 00:14:01,850
Sure, right.

278
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:03,580
At least I won't spend as much then.

279
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:04,600
Later.

280
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:12,450
I have to admit, thanks to those signs Lexa brought from work, you sell more than when you talk.

281
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:18,950
Excuse me, do you have the new Britney Spears?

282
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:33,650
Come on, it smells weird in here anyway.

283
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:46,270
Were you out shopping?

284
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:47,970
I went to check on Ivuska.

285
00:14:48,170 --> 00:14:49,190
She looked really nice.

286
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:52,150
She smiled at me like she hasn't in a long time.

287
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,250
I'm really proud of her.

288
00:14:54,410 --> 00:14:55,910
I'm glad the kids are working too.

289
00:14:56,050 --> 00:14:57,870
They even got free work overalls, right?

290
00:14:58,650 --> 00:15:01,150
Sweet girl, above the register it says ask me anything.

291
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:04,050
So I asked her when she's coming home.

292
00:15:06,950 --> 00:15:09,480
She said 538 flat.

293
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:12,740
Either way, if they keep doing this well, I'll ditch the Badger.

294
00:15:12,740 --> 00:15:13,100
And?

295
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:17,040
So far I'm only charging them water and sewage, but I'll add electricity and gas.

296
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:20,560
Which reminds me, you promised to pay for Ozzak.

297
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:21,520
1062.

298
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:25,350
Well, the situation has sort of developed.

299
00:15:25,850 --> 00:15:26,650
I don't have it now.

300
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:31,480
At a party in '88 you promised you'd never leave me hanging.

301
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,380
You keep doing it!

302
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:35,330
I hope you don't also have some kind of list.

303
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:49,760
Does a chicken and a turkey look the same to you?

304
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:52,850
Some idiot stole all the signs and everyone keeps asking me.

305
00:15:53,450 --> 00:15:53,930
Hi.

306
00:15:53,930 --> 00:15:55,450
Hi, hey uncle.

307
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:58,350
Where'd you get this?

308
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:01,230
Lexa?

309
00:16:02,050 --> 00:16:04,850
Jesus, he'll have to return it or I'll have to report him.

310
00:16:04,850 --> 00:16:06,790
Oh great, miss inspector.

311
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:07,670
I can't help it.

312
00:16:07,670 --> 00:16:11,070
The boss said I'm perfect for it, nobody notices me.

313
00:16:11,070 --> 00:16:12,050
How are you doing?

314
00:16:12,750 --> 00:16:14,160
At least you don't get those people.

315
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:15,380
It's always the same types.

316
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:19,220
Argumentative grannies, confused old dudes, sweaty stinkers.

317
00:16:19,550 --> 00:16:22,040
So you're happy when someone normal shows up.

318
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,040
Like who?

319
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:24,020
Like me.

320
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:25,820
You're a classic confused old dude.

321
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:27,980
By the time you find your change, my shift is over.

322
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:28,960
Iva.

323
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,120
Argumentative grannies.

324
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:34,700
Who come to argue because in the flyer spinach is one crown cheaper.

325
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:35,740
That's the worst.

326
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:38,000
Iva, you shouldn't talk about customers like that.

327
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:39,040
I don't see why not.

328
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:40,560
And you don't smile enough.

329
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,820
We're not at work right now.

330
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:46,010
I can't take it anymore, I'm done.

331
00:16:46,350 --> 00:16:48,150
Being an adult isn't easy, is it?

332
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:50,450
And it's not worth it either.

333
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:53,750
Walk away, run from the first problem.

334
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:57,120
Fine, I'll stick it out two more weeks.

335
00:16:57,650 --> 00:17:00,240
But I need a different register, I'd go crazy here.

336
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:02,350
I've got the speaker right above my head.

337
00:17:02,850 --> 00:17:07,490
Register seven open, register four open, register five open.

338
00:17:07,490 --> 00:17:09,250
You look uptight, I'll make you cocoa.

339
00:17:10,850 --> 00:17:11,650
Cocoa, so you wake up better.

340
00:17:14,340 --> 00:17:15,880
Cleanup on seven, hurry up.

341
00:17:22,050 --> 00:17:23,950
The boss said I shouldn't complain.

342
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:39,860
The time has come.

343
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:57,550
What is this?

344
00:17:58,050 --> 00:18:00,250
The Lostice Miracle.

345
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:03,470
In the Olomouc region, in the seventeenth century it supposedly...

346
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:09,250
Brought a dead farmhand back to life.

347
00:18:11,850 --> 00:18:13,070
Lucky he can't smell anything.

348
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:17,970
And when you bet in Moravia that you'd drink a bottle of plum brandy through your nose?

349
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:18,390
Right?

350
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:20,550
He won.

351
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:23,250
He's had burnt sinuses ever since.

352
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:24,620
Wait.

353
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:27,750
So, Marcelka, can I serve you a portion?

354
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:32,040
You don't even have to, it'll come out on its own.

355
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:35,200
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

356
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,220
I'll never allow this in the shop again.

357
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:43,410
Well, maybe, if you say so, maybe.

358
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:44,590
Alright then.

359
00:18:46,150 --> 00:18:48,550
And you, bro, have some too.

360
00:18:49,950 --> 00:18:52,350
What? I can't hear anything.

361
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:52,980
What?

362
00:18:56,350 --> 00:18:57,110
Guess he doesn't want any.

363
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:57,830
Never mind.

364
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,050
Vitamins?

365
00:19:04,650 --> 00:19:06,950
He probably wants a banana.

366
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:14,170
I still can't hear anything.

367
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:17,950
And yet one simple yes would be more than enough.

368
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:27,450
Marcelka, such a delicacy requires a proper beverage.

369
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:33,850
What, you want to tell us something, bro?

370
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:41,040
I understand, but unfortunately I couldn't carry more.

371
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:42,150
Here you go.

372
00:19:54,850 --> 00:19:55,850
So how did it go?

373
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:58,150
In a few days I'll be cashier of the month.

374
00:19:59,550 --> 00:20:01,650
I'll finally get out of that horrible register seven.

375
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:04,350
And I'll have my photo on the wall.

376
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:06,470
Today there was only one small incident.

377
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:08,250
You shouldn't have yelled at that lady.

378
00:20:08,530 --> 00:20:10,050
She dumped ice cream on the belt.

379
00:20:10,050 --> 00:20:12,390
Well, that's not such a disaster.

380
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:14,350
You know what ice cream does on the belt?

381
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:16,650
Then everything gets stuck together.

382
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,350
You know what the head cashier says?

383
00:20:18,430 --> 00:20:20,450
Swallow it, suck it up, and go scream it out in the tunnel.

384
00:20:22,050 --> 00:20:23,950
I waited five minutes for a rag.

385
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:26,450
I could have easily done three more carts in that time.

386
00:20:26,950 --> 00:20:28,440
You get points for carts.

387
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,980
Also for neat appearance.

388
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:35,040
And you got a bit disheveled during the yelling, so I had to dock you one point.

389
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:35,520
What?

390
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,740
And two for yelling at a customer.

391
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,360
She did that on purpose!

392
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,060
Even so, Iva, remember the 3Gs.

393
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,820
Greet, ask graciously, give thanks, and smile.

394
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:46,420
Come on, Ivuska, don't be sad.

395
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,700
Do you know where the pliers are?

396
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:51,450
Household goods department, third shelf.

397
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,240
Iva, enough.

398
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:57,000
This can't go on.

399
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:00,250
Here, take the money, buy a snowboard.

400
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:02,850
Marcelka from Harold won't get her bonus until next month.

401
00:21:03,350 --> 00:21:04,350
Don't you have anything smaller?

402
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:09,350
I want to be a good cashier.

403
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:11,350
Everyone keeps ruining it for me.

404
00:21:16,350 --> 00:21:16,850
People.

405
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:17,980
Hi.

406
00:21:18,650 --> 00:21:19,150
Lexa, you have to help me.

407
00:21:22,050 --> 00:21:22,950
I'm so hungry.

408
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:24,130
But I don't have any food.

409
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:26,350
I do, I bought gummy bears.

410
00:21:27,050 --> 00:21:31,350
They wouldn't let me near them in the warehouse, so when I tried to grab some, they fired me.

411
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:34,050
I can't lift my arms now.

412
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:48,650
Hey!

413
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:52,330
Three days went by like nothing and it didn't bother me at all.

414
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:53,250
Yeah, sure.

415
00:21:54,050 --> 00:21:55,650
Beer, brewsky, cold one.

416
00:21:56,490 --> 00:21:58,730
I can't understand how I lasted so long without those words.

417
00:21:59,150 --> 00:22:01,030
Marcelka, I urgently need to talk to you.

418
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:05,920
Ozzak has been talking to me all morning, but saying basically the same thing.

419
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,960
Twelve-pack, lager, dark, wheat beer.

420
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:11,100
Those words just caress the tongue, bro.

421
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,260
Marcelka, I'm worried about Iva.

422
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:15,180
I feel like she's overdoing it with the job.

423
00:22:15,650 --> 00:22:17,250
It's nice that she's trying.

424
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:19,850
Yesterday she put price tags on everything at home.

425
00:22:20,250 --> 00:22:22,150
And when she goes to the bathroom, she comes to ask my permission.

426
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:23,250
That is serious.

427
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:24,470
And she calls me sir.

428
00:22:25,450 --> 00:22:27,690
You have to get her out of there, or she'll go crazy.

429
00:22:27,690 --> 00:22:28,670
She won't listen.

430
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:32,230
Water, barley malt, hop products, lactic acid.

431
00:22:32,290 --> 00:22:35,670
Ozzak, remember how I once promised I'd never let you leave work early?

432
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:36,090
Yeah.

433
00:22:36,190 --> 00:22:36,950
Today you can.

434
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:38,150
Really?

435
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:38,410
Yeah.

436
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:39,050
Thanks.

437
00:22:39,650 --> 00:22:43,050
You know, there's one thing I understood during those long years of silence, bro.

438
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,180
Some promises are totally useless.

439
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:45,980
Let's go, bro.

440
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,140
Two words, that's all I missed, three days.

441
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:49,650
Now tell me, where are those cheese curds?

442
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:54,280
The health inspectors came and took them away for testing.

443
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:54,660
No!

444
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:57,420
They won't return them for at least a month.

445
00:22:58,450 --> 00:22:59,750
By then they'll be epic.

446
00:23:06,050 --> 00:23:09,450
Iva, you look terrible, smile a little.

447
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:13,950
I already had my photo taken for the wall.

448
00:23:16,150 --> 00:23:17,750
What happened?

449
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:26,250
The head manager fired me.

450
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:31,360
Well, you did your best.

451
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:32,160
I saw it myself.

452
00:23:32,850 --> 00:23:34,350
I had what it takes.

453
00:23:34,850 --> 00:23:37,250
I could have become cashier of the month.

454
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:41,600
Supposedly I don't smile enough at customers and don't give them enough plastic bags.

455
00:23:42,260 --> 00:23:45,820
I was at the register and could take as many bags as I wanted.

456
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:47,600
What do you say, aww.

457
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:48,940
Not seriously.

458
00:23:49,350 --> 00:23:51,050
And she smiled beautifully.

459
00:23:53,250 --> 00:23:54,750
And you know who ratted me out?

460
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:56,960
Sasa!

461
00:23:58,620 --> 00:23:59,100
Sasa?

462
00:23:59,370 --> 00:24:01,430
Are you sure Sasa would do that?

463
00:24:01,650 --> 00:24:03,670
I've lost my best friend.

464
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:07,810
Come on Ivuska, Harold isn't the only supermarket in the world.

465
00:24:08,150 --> 00:24:10,490
And you're still young, your whole life ahead of you.

466
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:14,450
But I love this one!

467
00:24:38,450 --> 00:24:41,850
So I'm going with the trash.

468
00:24:44,250 --> 00:24:46,150
How can you even show your face here?

469
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:48,440
Iva, I...

470
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:50,250
You're not my friend anymore.

471
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:52,600
You're a careerist, so I'm not surprised.

472
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:54,040
Sorry, Iva, I...

473
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:54,580
You're a hyena.

474
00:24:58,350 --> 00:24:59,750
I was worried about you.

475
00:25:00,150 --> 00:25:01,450
You changed so much.

476
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:04,170
All you cared about was the register and the wall.

477
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:04,970
That's not true.

478
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:09,650
You put up a sign in the locker room saying only weaklings go to the bathroom during work hours.

479
00:25:11,350 --> 00:25:14,550
And you volunteered for Saturday window washing.

480
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:18,750
Yesterday you even complimented the head manager on her new perm.

481
00:25:21,250 --> 00:25:23,690
I was afraid you were completely losing it.

482
00:25:24,450 --> 00:25:26,850
So I made up things to get you fired.

483
00:25:27,070 --> 00:25:27,650
What?

484
00:25:28,450 --> 00:25:31,690
I reported that you say "drop dead" to customers instead of goodbye.

485
00:25:31,690 --> 00:25:32,270
What?

486
00:25:32,850 --> 00:25:37,680
And that you threw a kilo of discounted mustard at a woman who complained.

487
00:25:38,050 --> 00:25:40,850
You know I hate lying, but for you I managed.

488
00:25:41,950 --> 00:25:44,150
So you did it to save me.

489
00:25:44,850 --> 00:25:46,980
I quit too, I won't be there without you.

490
00:25:47,450 --> 00:25:49,620
And I'll go skiing again with a sled, fine.

491
00:25:50,050 --> 00:25:52,050
Kropackova can kiss my ass.

492
00:26:01,650 --> 00:26:03,950
Bro, weren't you going to take out the trash?

493
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:07,050
I only said that to lighten the mood.

494
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:49,020
Bro, just like the old days!

495
00:26:51,250 --> 00:26:51,650
Do you still have those signs?

496
00:26:53,350 --> 00:26:54,850
I have a feeling I'm going to need them.
